About Einstein Discovery

Configure Projected Predictions

Einstein Discovery allows you to provide trending data for numeric variables that factor into your predictions to make them more accurate. For example, you predict opportunity win/loss based on expected price fluctuations for raw materials.

In Model Setup, select a number variable, and click the Settings tab in the right panel.
Click the Transform dropdown menu and select Projected Predictions.
Select the dataset that contains the trend data.
Configure the projected prediction settings:
Unique Identifier Column
Variable Column
Time Interval Column
Time Interval
Number of Intervals to Project Ahead
Seasonality
title: Configuring Projected Predictions in Einstein Discovery
